raw_data.title: Operations Research Systems Analyst Junior
raw_data.description: As part of a government or contractor led team, collects and analyzes data to evaluate operations and processes and facilitate information driven decision-making.  Utilizes operations research tools and methods including simulation to evaluate alternatives and develop recommendations to address customer's problems.  Follows established modeling and evaluation methodologies to determine the effectiveness of current operations, isolate problem areas and develop solutions.  Supports efforts to test and validate models and results.  Supports preparation of reports that specify and rank proposed solutions to present a range of possible alternatives.  Requires a Bachelor's degree and 3 years experience.  Typically reports to a government or contractor supervisor.
